										<v8:item>
											<v8:lang>en</v8:lang>
											<v8:content>Fuel capacity at the finish line in liters. Possible values:
- Fixed value - a fixed value in liters, less than the vehicle's full tank capacity;
- Maximum volume at the finish line - the maximum volume at the finish line;
- Minimum volume - the minimum volume is calculated as the minimum permissible tank capacity + fuel consumption per 100 km; this is selected when driving to a low-cost region;
- Shuttle route - the service will calculate the amount of fuel required for refueling to the finish line (plus a small reserve) and then for the return trip to the optimal gas station.</v8:content>
